Sure, here's a JavaScript function that swaps the case of each character in a given string:

```javascript
function swapCase(str) {
  return str.split('').map(char => {
    if (char === char.toUpperCase()) {
      return char.toLowerCase();
    } else {
      return char.toUpperCase();
    }
  }).join('');
}

// Example usage:
console.log(swapCase("Hello World")); // "hELLO wORLD"
```

This function works by splitting the input string into an array of characters, then mapping each character to its opposite case, and finally joining the array back into a string.
